content.location: Located between Hilti Highway and The Sting.

content.description: The crux moves are at the very beginning and once you reach the large vertical jug/fissure to the left of the starting holds, the grade softens.
content.location: To the right of Dead Cats Wall, this climb is located about 6 ft to the left of a prominent beehive halfway up the cliff.  In cold weather the bees tend to be a good bit less active.

content.description: Fun moves off the ground to the first bolt, reaching bolt two is the technical crux of the route.  From there you go right to the third bolt.  Though slightly runout, the climbing to the anchors from this point is easy.
content.location: This route is located on the face about 15 ft to the right of the Mammazz Boyzz dihedral.  To find it you're probably best off starting at Serpent's Wall and going along the base of the cliff till you find the first bolt OR locating the behive midway up the cliff (and to the right of Dead Cat's Wall) and going 20ft to the right of that beehive along the base of the cliff.

content.description: Start with small seam and work above to slightly sloping small holds.
content.location: two routes to the right of "the sting" and the infamous bee hive. dun dun dun

content.description: Traverse a little left at the start, then enjoy a nice break in a huge deep hueco before heading up for the finish.
content.location: Left side of the annex, just a little right of Mex.

content.description: Wall on right side of Dead Cats and  70 feet left of Serpent Wall.   Mostly shady.
